4/
And service providers compete in an open market, which will further drive the innovation and UX. Only this will drive the next 1billion adoption of web3.

3/
To provide both ownership and user experience, a token-centric framework like @TokenScript is a must-have. With services integrated on the user side via tokens, each user will have his/her fully integrated web, which can provide him/her 100 x better UX than web2.

2/
To have better Web3 UX in the DApp framework, centralized platform-based integration is expected, then it will go back to the "platform owns everything" situation. And the best UX this can get is exactly the same as web2, no more.

Ownership and user experience are the key drivers of Web3 adoption.
